1.10.3 [4 Mar 2006]
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
	+ Fixed missing DESTDIR in doc/Makefile (thanks Dan Nicholson).
	+ Tested successfully with gcc-4.0.0.
	+ Removed porg.spec from the tarball. Created porg.pc. This allows for
	  retrieving the porg log directory after installation with pkg-config,
	  like this: "pkg-config --variable=logdir porg".
	+ Allowed the use of option '-x|--expand' when logging packages. If the
	  expansion leads to more than one package name, porg prints an error
	  message and exits. See an example in the README file.
	+ Scripts are no longer included in the distribution. They have been
	  available in the web site (http://porg.sourceforge.net/downloads.html).
	+ [bugfix]: temporary files were not always removed at exit.
	+ Removed the option '--with-porg-logdir' in configure, since it can be set
	  in the configuration file.
	+ New options CLEAR_EMPTY and CLEAR_UNINSTALLED for porgrc. See the man page
	  of porgrc for more information.
	+ Minor bugfixes.


